Description: 
    A self-contained toolchain for single-sample germline variant calls
    annotated with Ensembl VEP, SnpEff, or both. Converts per-sample VCFs
    into an MAF-like 'data.table' (one row per ALT allele, one
    most-severe transcript per allele) via three sibling readers that
    share a canonical 80-field schema and are auto-routed from the VCF
    header. Cohort folders are processed in parallel with a live
    heartbeat. Adds optional Brazilian ABraOM SABE-609 allele-frequency
    annotation, a curated disease gene-panel registry, and modular
    toggleable filtering by population-frequency, clinical significance,
    biotype, variant classification, genotype, and panel. A dedicated
    subsetter isolates candidate novel variants (no rsID, no population
    AF in any catalogue). Generates a multi-section cohort summary with
    optional 'Excel' workbook, multi-page 'PDF', and self-contained
    interactive 'HTML' dashboard featuring 'plotly' drill-downs and 'DT'
    tables; a 'ComplexHeatmap'-based top-genes variant matrix; per-section
    standalone plot exports plus multi-panel composites; per-gene protein-domain
    lollipop plots with on-the-fly InterPro domain fetching (cached);
    per-gene gene-structure (cDNA) lollipop plots with Ensembl REST or
    local GTF sources (cached); and a unified 52-palette colour system
    with colourblind-safe defaults shared across every figure.
